                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850d.00/288.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reply of President [of the Conference] presenting modified pro jet de convention
                    prepared by the three northern Powers in the preliminary conference states that
                    American plan has been considered but cannot be used as a substitute since it is
                    conceived in the terms of Anglo-American jurisprudence, is in English, and
                    besides all other nations have used only the three-power projets as bases for
                    their study of Spitzbergen questions. We fear that its presentation might cause
                    unfavorable feeling and delay. If however Department wishes it presented
                    translation should be made in Washington with the care given to the preparation
                    of official text of treaties, and with a view to the necessary attendant delay
                    before the receipt of printed copies. But we believe it best to use it, for the
                    present, as a guide in suggesting amendments to their plans. We request
                    telegraphic instructions as next session is on Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>.</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Collier</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
